"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"目前在網路上可以找到蠻多toki pona的字典，大致上是大同小異，因為光是用這123個單字的排列組合，已經可以組合出日常生活溝通用的句子、物品，甚至是交通工具。\\n\\n其實我在一開始學習toki pona時，會因為toki pona這只有123個單字而感到困惑，到底要怎麼做才能夠光靠這123個單字來進行日常生活的互動與一些物品、科技用品的表達？\\n\\n但當我慢慢體會到toki pona的精髓後，我發現，使用toki pona時不要想太多，也不要想的太複雜，自然就可以順利的使用，譬如：\\n\\n1. tomo:空間、房子 \\n tawa:移動、運輸 \\n tomo tawa:汽車\\n2. tomo:空間、房子 \\n tawa:移動、運輸 \\n kon:空氣、風、氣體 \\n tomo tawa kon:飛機\\n3. tomo:空間、房子 \\n tawa:移動、運輸 \\n supa:水平表面、板子 \\n tomo tawa supa:船\\n4. telo:水 \\n kili:水果 \\n telo kili:果汁\\n5. telo:水 \\n nasa:瘋狂 \\n telo nasa:酒 \\n \\n\\n也在這裡放上幾個我認為整理的很不錯的網路字典：（toki pona:英文、印尼文、日文） \\n 一、<https://jprogr.github.io/TokiPonaDictionary/> \\n  \\n 二、<https://glosbe.com/en/mis_tok>\\n\\n三、<https://devurandom.xyz/tokipona/dictionary.html>\\n\\n四、<https://theotherwebsite.com/tokipona/>\\n\\n紙本的字典亞馬遜上有在賣，運來台灣的話，書+運費大概要一千多台幣：[Toki Pona Dictionary (Official Toki Pona)](https://www.amazon.com/Toki-Pona-Dictionary-Official/dp/0978292367)\\n\\n接下來就貼上我自己整理的toki pona字典，我是用自己方便記憶的排列方式重新排列過，也是toki pona與英文對翻。\\n\\ntoki pona與中文對翻目前只有在[萌娘百科](https://go.caishin.com/3wuae4)上看到，若大家有需要，可以到[萌娘百科](https://go.caishin.com/3wuae4)上看：[lipu pi toki pona tan jan Maku](https://go.caishin.com/3wuae4)\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n**toki pona dictionary**\\n\\nijo：thing, phenomenon, object, matter\\n\\nkulupu：community, company, group, nation, society, tribe\\n\\n \\n \\n\\npilin：heart (physical or emotional)。feeling (an emotion, a direct experience)\\n\\nolin：to love, have compassion for, respect, show affection to\\n\\nwile：must, need, require, should, want, wish\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nakesi：non-cute animal; reptile, amphibian\\n\\npipi：bug, insect, ant, spider\\n\\nsoweli：animal, beast, land mammal\\n\\nwaso：bird, flying creature, winged animal\\n\\nkala：fish, marine animal, sea creature\\n\\nmu：(animal noise or communication)\\n\\n \\n \\n\\ntawa：going to, toward; for; from the perspective of。moving\\n\\nawen：enduring, kept, protected, safe, waiting, staying。to continue to\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nkama：arriving, coming, future, summoned。to become, manage to, succeed in\\n\\nweka：absent, away, ignored\\n\\npini：ago, completed, ended, finished, past\\n\\n \\n \\n\\njan：human being, person, somebody\\n\\nmeli：woman, female, feminine person; wife\\n\\nmije：man, male, masculine person; husband\\n\\nsama：same, similar; each other; sibling, peer, fellow\\n\\nunpa：to have sexual or marital relations with\\n\\nmama：parent, ancestor; creator, originator; caretaker, sustainer\\n\\nmoli：dead, dying\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nwawa：strong, powerful; confident, sure; energetic, intense\\n\\njo：to have, carry, contain, hold\\n\\nken：to be able to, be allowed to, can, may。possible\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nmi：I, me, we, us\\n\\nsina：you\\n\\nona：he, she, it, they\\n\\nlape：sleeping, resting\\n\\nmusi：artistic, entertaining, frivolous, playful, recreational\\n\\n \\n \\n\\npona：good, positive, useful; friendly, peaceful; simple\\n\\nike：bad, negative; non-essential, irrelevant\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nlawa：head, mind。to control, direct, guide, lead, own, plan, regulate, rule\\n\\noko：eye。to look at, see, examine, observe, read, watch。to seek, look for, try to\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nlukin：eye。to look at, see, examine, observe, read, watch。to seek, look for, try to\\n\\nnena：bump, button, hill, mountain, nose, protuberance\\n\\nuta：mouth, lips, oral cavity, jaw\\n\\nkute：ear。to hear, listen; pay attention to, obey\\n\\nsinpin：face, foremost, front, wall\\n\\nluka：arm, hand, tactile organ\\n\\nnoka：foot, leg, organ of locomotion; bottom, lower part\\n\\nsijelo：body (of person or animal), physical state, torso\\n\\ninsa：centre, content, inside, between; internal organ, stomach\\n\\nselo：outer form, outer layer; bark, peel, shell, skin; boundary\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nlen：cloth, clothing, fabric, textile; cover, layer of privacy\\n\\n \\n \\n\\npali：to do, take action on, work on; build, make, prepare\\n\\nmoku：to eat, drink, consume, swallow, ingest\\n\\nkepeken：to use, with, by means of\\n\\npana：to give, send, emit, provide, put, release\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nmun：moon, night sky object, star\\n\\nsuno：sun; light, brightness, glow, radiance, shine; light source\\n\\nma：earth, land; outdoors, world; country, territory; soil\\n\\nkasi：plant, vegetation; herb, leaf\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nkiwen：hard object, metal, rock, stone\\n\\nko：clay, clinging form, dough, semi-solid, paste, powder\\n\\ntelo：water, liquid, fluid, wet substance; beverage\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nkon：air, breath; essence, spirit; hidden reality, unseen agent\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nseli：fire; cooking element, chemical reaction, heat source\\n\\nlete：cold, cool; uncooked, raw\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nsewi：area above, highest part, something elevated。awe-inspiring, divine, sacred, supernatural\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nkule：colourful, pigmented, painted\\n\\nloje：red, reddish\\n\\njelo：yellow, yellowish\\n\\nlaso：blue, green\\n\\nwalo：white, whitish; light-coloured, pale\\n\\npimeja：black, dark, unlit\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nlili：little, small, short; few; a bit; young\\n\\nsuli：big, heavy, large, long, tall; important; adult\\n\\n \\n \\n\\npan：cereal, grain; barley, corn, oat, rice, wheat; bread, pasta\\n\\nkili：fruit, vegetable, mushroom\\n\\nsuwi：sweet, fragrant; cute, innocent, adorable\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nalasa：to hunt, forage\\n\\nilo：tool, implement, machine, device\\n\\n \\n \\n\\ntomo：indoor space; building, home, house, room\\n\\nlupa：door, hole, orifice, window\\n\\npoki：container, bag, bowl, box, cup, cupboard, drawer, vessel\\n\\nsupa：horizontal surface, thing to put or rest something on\\n\\nopen：to begin, start; open; turn on\\n\\n \\n \\n\\ntenpo：time, duration, moment, occasion, period, situation\\n\\nsike：round or circular thing; ball, circle, cycle, sphere, wheel。of one year\\n\\n \\n \\n\\npalisa：long hard thing; branch, rod, stick\\n\\nlinja：long and flexible thing; cord, hair, rope, thread, yarn\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nnasa：unusual, strange; foolish, crazy; drunk, intoxicated\\n\\njaki：disgusting, obscene, sickly, toxic, unclean, unsanitary\\n\\npakala：botched, broken, damaged, harmed, messed up\\n\\nutala：to battle, challenge, compete against, struggle against\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nsin：new, fresh; additional, another, extra\\n\\nnamako：new, fresh; additional, another, extra\\n\\ntoki：to communicate, say, speak, talk, use language, think\\n\\nkalama：music, sound, to produce a sound; recite, utter aloud\\n\\nsona：to know, be skilled in, be wise about, have information on。to know how to\\n\\nlipu：flat object; book, document, card, paper, record, website\\n\\nsitelen：image, picture, representation, symbol, mark, writing\\n\\nnimi：name, word\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nnanpa：-th (ordinal number)。numbers\\n\\nala：no, not, zero\\n\\nwan：unique, united。one\\n\\ntu：two\\n\\nmute：many, a lot, more, much, several, very。quantity\\n\\nali：all; abundant, countless, bountiful, every, plentiful。abundance, everything, life, universe。100\\n\\nale：all; abundant, countless, bountiful, every, plentiful。abundance, everything, life, universe。100\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nmani：money, cash, savings, wealth; large domesticated animal\\n\\nesun：market, shop, fair, bazaar, business transaction\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nlon：located at, present at, real, true, existing\\n\\npoka：hip, side; next to, nearby, vicinity\\n\\nanpa：bowing down, downward, humble, lowly, dependent\\n\\nsinpin：face, foremost, front, wall\\n\\nmonsi：back, behind, rear\\n\\ninsa：centre, content, inside, between; internal organ, stomach\\n\\nsupa：horizontal surface, thing to put or rest something on\\n\\nselo：outer form, outer layer; bark, peel, shell, skin; boundary\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nni：that, this\\n\\ntan：by, from, because of\\n\\nnasin：way, custom, doctrine, method, path, road\\n\\n \\n \\n\\na：emotion word\\n\\nkin：emotion word\\n\\no：hey! O! (vocative or imperative)\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nsama：same, similar; each other; sibling, peer, fellow\\n\\nante：different, altered, changed, other\\n\\n \\n \\n\\nen：(between multiple subjects)\\n\\nli：(between any subject except mi alone or sina alone and its verb; also to introduce a new verb for the same subject)\\n\\ne：(before the direct object)\\n\\nla：(between the context phrase and the main sentence)\\n\\npi：of\\n\\nanu：or\\n\\nseme：what? which?\\n\\ntaso：but, however。only\\n\\n \\n \\n\\npu：interacting with the official Toki Pona book\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n![](https://assets.matters.news/embed/73f6fd90-0adf-48dd-b828-fe723968b7bb.jpeg)\\n\\n\",\"timestamp\":1642165438,\"title\":\"toki pona 的字典\"},\"digest\":\"LSA1n_5m2QrSPtx4SpSGxf-SnsFmBh6YvaivG1XktBo\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xC6fEb0bf7Bc1D065c944734C4032a240b5aB2DAc\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"vEbnvG8j0arxOj7FWDBoPTrOsj8ztPQheaiOlcy9ulw\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"nBnVyNvDGugu7fUXpNfA3JMJ4eDCnXWWkDm5ONxQMYg\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"6dx-Ls1nlNJrMKOYlZ3KKrXkxpZEOtDdp7Ax9z0cROAR3nnbKX7AKEUorWRTiX7naCQtDxtU4HozU2OTf6MvlQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xc5584cc892d2cb9af27b4a0b2f40aa43d1fc37012118975a722ff63833cd44b37aad3e7840b6eaf2f32a3dce6a9d84538c8b769ea75b4fd41de58bb496b455ee1b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"vEbnvG8j0arxOj7FWDBoPTrOsj8ztPQheaiOlcy9ulw\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"nBnVyNvDGugu7fUXpNfA3JMJ4eDCnXWWkDm5ONxQMYg\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"LSA1n_5m2QrSPtx4SpSGxf-SnsFmBh6YvaivG1XktBo\"}"